ntaining and challenging imagined communities and focuses upon the ways in which performance contributes to people's sense of the kinds of use for which dialect/variational use is appropriate and those for which it is not. It sheds light on how such stylization intersects with multiple social indexes and how performers and other creative artists challenge and mock hegemonic practices through enregistering a defined set of linguistic variables in the context of their performance and other associated written texts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aEnregisterment.  aLinguistic Variation.  aPerformance.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton Contemporary 2016-2019z978311074297808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2019 Englishz978311061030708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2019z9783110606287oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97815015066970 cprintz978150151541540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150150679640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501506796423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501506796.jpg  a978-3-11-061030-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-071956-7  DG Plus eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-074297-8  De Gruyter Mouton Contemporary 2016-2019c2016d2019  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  